      • getDataVisibility

        public java.lang.String getDataVisibility()
        Get the data visibility. "Data visibility" is an application specific definition of how contact data may be used. An example use-case would be to define an enum with fields meaning 'internal', 'emergency-only', and 'public-website' and then set this string to one of the enum field names. Type-safety has been intentionally sacrificed for the benefit of providing applications a simple way to store application specific information in way that is searchable and does not require sub-typing value objects. Its strongly recommended that names of enum fields be stored in this String property instead of arbitrary hard-coded string literals.
        Specified by:
        getDataVisibility in interface PersonalInformation
        Returns:
        the data visibility, which won't be null but could be empty string.
